description.priceChange: The difference between the current price and the previous day's settlement price.
description.percentChange: The difference between the current price and the previous day's settlement price expressed as a percentage.
description.optionsTotalVolume: The total volume for all option contracts (across all expiration dates) traded during the current session.
description.optionsPutCallVolumeRatio: The total Put/Call volume ratio for all option contracts (across all expiration dates) traded during the current session.
description.historicVolatility30d: 30-Day Historical Volatility: The average deviation from the average price over the last 30 days.
description.optionsWeightedImpliedVolatility: The average implied volatility (IV) of the nearest monthly options contract that is 30-days out or more. A green implied volatility means it is increasing compared to yesterday, and a red implied volatility means it is decreasing compared to yesterday.
description.optionsImpliedVolatilityRank1y: The ATM average implied volatility relative to the highest and lowest values over the past 1-year. If IV Rank is 100% this means the IV is at its highest level over the past 1-year.
description.optionsImpliedVolatilityPercentile1y: IV Percentile: The percentage of days with implied volatility closing below the current ATM IV over the prior 1-year.
description.optionsWeightedImpliedVolatilityChange: The underlying asset's change in Implied Volatility for the current trading session.
description.symbolType: A Call option gives you the right to buy a stock and a Put option gives you the right to sell a stock.
description.hasOptions: The symbol either has options available, or does not.
